After a night of drinks in the Galley on the Belfast city water front, a friend tried out some photo work with a flower bud and a candle. Watching him play with the light and the glow the candle it made me think of some photos I could produce with a set of candles at home and try and reproduce the same glowing light and shadows. Below are some of the images from the session. For the images I used a mix of a Canon EF 38-76mm F/4.5-5.6 and a Olympu Zuiko 50mm f1.8, as the Olympu is manual focus I had issues getting the focus on spot but in some images this added to the look i was going for. Many images have been post processed with LightRoom.

