Back again with the LOFT group shutter speed met in the LOFT studio to tackle some texture and tone work, with an extra challenge of not using macro. As known for most instances of texture photography everyone will grab their macro lens or switch their camera into macro mode. This makes things too easy and something as simple a sheet of white paper will look stunning in a macro shot taking the skill and thought behind the shot out of the equation. Now that marco is not an option people have to start thinking more about composer, lighting and the story behind the image. It was a challenge but I managed to get some nice results shown below, all shot on a Canon 400D with a 50mm 1.4 prime.

